      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The ongoing conflict between the US and Iran, referred to as Operation Epic Fury, is characterized by multiple military actions, including drone strikes, air refueling runs, and missile launches. The US military is experiencing significant losses, with estimates ranging from $1.4 billion to $3 billion, and is working to adapt and respond to the changing situation. The conflict is having a broader impact, with implications for global security and stability, and the potential for long-term consequences for the region and the world. The US is attempting to negotiate a way out of the crisis, but Iran has publicly dismissed these efforts. The situation remains volatile, with the potential for further escalation and expansion of the conflict. The US military is also focused on improving its acquisition systems and supporting its troops and capabilities in the region, while facing criticism for its actions and questions about the use of military might as a tool of aggression.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
